HEADWORD: Aluminium
<hw>Al`u*min"i*um</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧l`⟦usl⟧*m⟦icr⟧n"⟦icr⟧*⟦ucr⟧m)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>alumen</ets>. See <er>Alum</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>same as <er>aluminum</er>, chiefly British in
usage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Aluminium bronze</b></col> or
<col><b>gold</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a pale gold-colored alloy of
aluminium and copper, used for journal bearings, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

